# 60_actions_step_repeat_smoke — Tier 2 m10 Step-and-repeat sweep (s255).
# Validates the one wrap-now Step-and-repeat verb migrated from raw
# `add_action` to `add_scripted_action`:
#   - step-repeat
#
# Sibling smoke to 52-59, same conservative-shape posture. Parameterless;
# default Scripter | TestRunner mask. Per audit fork #5: this is a
# hand-off point to a future `selection.step_repeat(...)` parameterised
# verb on a selection-Scriptable that doesn't exist yet; the action
# launches a dialog whose Apply path does the work.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Four observables: 1 list + 1 invocation + 2 refusals.
#
# ── Caller / mask ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ScripterWindow listener, RunContext::Scripter. Macro is OUT.
#
# ── Test isolation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# `win step-repeat` calls on_step_repeat() which launches the step-repeat
# dialog. Trace channel says `ok` as soon as the dialog is shown
# (synchronous launch); visual channel: dialog opens. The user / future
# selection-Scriptable would then drive the dialog's Apply path. For
# this smoke, the dialog opening IS the visual confirmation; close it
# manually after the run.
#
# ── Precondition reminders ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Curvz running with project + doc open.
# 2. A dialog will appear after phase 2 — close it before continuing
#    other work. The smoke's remaining phases (refusals) run regardless.

#[sub] === Phase 1: registry sanity-check — `win` is still registered ===

list

#[sub] === Phase 2: step-repeat verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Calls on_step_repeat(); visual: step-repeat dialog opens.
#[sub] Trace channel reports `ok` as soon as the dialog is presented.

win step-repeat

#[sub] === Phase 3: unknown-verb refusal ===

win quit

#[sub] === Phase 4: extra-argument refusal ===

win step-repeat "argument"

